<paragraph id="8BC1DA58FF97FFDBFE98FA6C0D84F9E0" blockId="3.[264,1323,1462,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Relationships: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF97FFDBFE46FA6D0D99FA78" box="[486,697,1463,1488]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="songi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF97FFDBFE46FA6D0D99FA78" box="[486,697,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Mesobuthus songi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A239BB31FF97FFDBFD60FA6C0DDEFA78" box="[704,766,1462,1488]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is undoubtedly associated with the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF97FFDBFB3DFA6D0D1AFA50" authority="Fabricius, 1798" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamulus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF97FFDBFB3DFA6D0E44FA50" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Mesobuthus tamulus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF97FFDBFE56FA040D12FA50" box="[502,562,1502,1528]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1798.0">1798</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
group of species. It can, however, be distinguished from other species of this group, and in particular from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA1DBFF97FFDBFC96F9DD0E6FF9E0" authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="tamulus" subSpecies="gangeticus">
<emphasis id="B90A064AFF97FFDBFC96F9DD0B98F988" box="[822,1208,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Mesobuthus tamulus gangeticus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA7A9FF97FFDBFB6BF9DC0E66F9E0" author="Pocock" pageId="3" pageNumber="15" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1900) The scorpions of the genus Heterometrus. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (7) 5, 362 - 365." type="journal article" year="1900">
Pocock, 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF97FFDBFEA8F9F40E66F9E0" box="[264,326,1582,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1900.0">1900</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, by the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1DA58FF97FFDBFE98F98C0BF3F8B8" blockId="3.[264,1323,1462,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
(i) smaller size; 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF97FFDBFE5AF98C0D37F9D8" box="[506,535,1622,1648]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="66.0">66</number>
and 
<quantity id="4C8677BDFF97FFDBFDF4F98C0D87F9D8" box="[596,679,1622,1648]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="68.0">68 mm</quantity>
in total length against 
<number id="3DB6C87FFF97FFDBFC1CF98C0CF9F9D8" box="[956,985,1622,1648]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="71.0">71</number>
and 
